SIMPLE: mineralization
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mineralization
<hw>Min`er*al*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>min⟦eacute⟧ralisation</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The process of mineralizing, or forming a mineral by
combination of a metal with another element; also, the process of
converting into a mineral, as a bone or a plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of impregnating with a mineral, as
water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The conversion of a cell wall into
a material of a stony nature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mineralize</ent>⟦br⟧
